---
description: FT Design System implementation guardrails
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- Read relevant files in `specs/` before writing or modifying UI code.
- Do not build placeholders or generic components.
- Do not deviate from Figma-backed design contracts.
- Do not create unsupported variations.
- Never use hardcoded visual values unless explicitly requested and documented.
- Run token checks before commit: `npm run check:tokens`.
- Run consistency checks before commit for UI/component changes: `npm run check:consistency`.
- Run explorer inspector coverage check for explorer config/story updates: `npm run check:explorer-inspector`.
- New component layout stories must include `parameters.explorer.inspector` config with valid `defaultMode`.
- Before publishing, run `npm run publish:prepare` (includes `npm run sync:docs`).
- Follow the PR review checklist at `specs/review-checklist.md` before approving or merging.
